javadoc:
Command for renaming labels. Handles converting back and forth between
 default and named labels as well.

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Constructs a new command for renaming a label within a specified namespace.

params.name: addr
params.comment: Address of label to be renamed.

params.name: oldName
params.comment: the current name of the label to be renamed.

params.name: newName
params.comment: the new name for the label. (null for default)

params.name: currentNamespace
params.comment: the symbol's current name space. (The namespace to associate this label with)

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment:
Constructs a new command for renaming a label within currentNamespace and changing the
 namespace to newNamespace.

params.name: addr
params.comment: Address of label to be renamed.

params.name: oldName
params.comment: the current name of the label to be renamed.

params.name: newName
params.comment: the new name for the label. (null for default)

params.name: currentNamespace
params.comment: the symbol's current parent name space (null indicates global namespace)

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Constructs a new command for renaming global labels.

params.name: addr
params.comment: Address of label to be renamed.

params.name: oldName
params.comment:
the name of the label to be renamed; may be null
 of the existing label is a dynamic label

params.name: newName
params.comment: the new name for the label

name: RenameLabelCmd
comment:
Command for renaming labels. Handles converting back and forth between
 default and named labels as well.
